settings.custom_liquid:
{% comment %}
  Template: Cookie Policy
  This page provides information about how we use cookies on Trezon's website.
{% endcomment %}

<div class="cookie-policy-container">
  <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>

  <section class="cookie-section">
    <h2>1. What are Cookies?</h2>
    <p>Cookies are small files that are placed on your device when you visit a website. They are used to make websites work more efficiently and provide information to the website owners. Cookies help us improve your experience on our site and remember certain preferences.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="cookie-section">
    <h2>2. How We Use Cookies</h2>
    <p>At Trezon, we use cookies to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Enhance your browsing experience on our site.</li>
      <li>Remember your preferences (such as language or location).</li>
      <li>Improve website functionality and performance.</li>
      <li>Track and analyze the effectiveness of our marketing campaigns.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="cookie-section">
    <h2>3. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
    <p>We use the following types of cookies:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> These are necessary for the functioning of our website and cannot be switched off in our systems.</li>
      <li><strong>Performance Cookies:</strong> These cookies allow us to track website usage and improve the website's performance.</li>
      <li><strong>Functional Cookies:</strong> These cookies allow us to remember choices you make (such as your username or language preferences).</li>
      <li><strong>Targeting Cookies:</strong> These cookies are used to deliver personalized advertisements or content based on your interests.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="cookie-section">
    <h2>4. How to Manage Cookies</h2>
    <p>You can control how cookies are used on your device by adjusting your browser settings. Most browsers allow you to block or delete cookies, but doing so may affect your experience on our website. To learn more about how to manage cookies, you can refer to your browserâ€™s help section.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="cookie-section">
    <h2>5. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
    <p>We may also use third-party services (such as Google Analytics or advertising networks) that may place cookies on your device. These cookies help us analyze website usage and provide personalized content and ads. These third-party cookies are governed by the privacy policies of the third-party providers.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="cookie-section">
    <h2>6. Updates to This Cookie Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update our cookie policy from time to time to reflect changes in technology or legal requirements. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last Updated" date.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="cookie-section">
    <h2>7. Need Help?</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions or concerns about our cookie policy, please contact us at <a href="mailto:trezon.in@gmail.com">trezon.in@gmail.com</a></p>
  </section>
</div>

<style>
  .cookie-policy-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 20px;
    background: #EEDFA4; /* Background color */
    border-radius: 10px;
  }
  .cookie-section {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .cookie-section h2 {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: bold;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .cookie-section p, .cookie-section ul {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: #333;
  }
  .cookie-section ul {
    list-style-type: disc;
    margin-left: 20px;
  }
  .cookie-section a {
    color: #392D00;
    font-weight: bold;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .cookie-section a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
